<paragraph id="3A4B5872932BFFBCCDD687B5FEFDFB42" blockId="4.[151,649,1180,1239]" box="[151,308,1214,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
(
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F7932BFFBCCDDE87B5FECAFB42" box="[159,259,1214,1239]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
Figs 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCD9687B5FECAFB42" box="[215,259,1214,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="5.74" valueMax="6.48" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F7932BFFBCCC4E87B4FEE5FB42" box="[271,300,1215,1239]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">48</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B5872932BFFBCCDD6860CFB95FAD6" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
A single male belonging this species was collected in 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCFAE860CFCEEFA8A" box="[751,807,1287,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2014.0">2014</number>
flying about five meters from the ground around 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCC80F860DFAA0FA8A" box="[1358,1385,1286,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="13.0">13</number>
:00h in the same place and time where males of 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCF3B8621FC06FAD6" authority="Seitz, 1913" authorityName="Seitz" authorityYear="1913" box="[634,975,1322,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rothschildi">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCF3B8621FCFEFAD6" box="[634,823,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Alesa rothschildi</emphasis>
(Seitz, 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCECC8620FC0FFAD6" box="[909,966,1323,1347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1913.0">1913</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
were found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B5872932BFFBCCD868645FBE0F9F6" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
This species was described from Bogotá, 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E2932BFFBCCFE98645FCDFFAF2" box="[680,790,1358,1383]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Colombia</collectingCountry>
based on a male and a female deposited at the 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCC8008644FA50FAF3" box="[1345,1433,1359,1382]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">BMNH</collectionCode>
. Apparently the record from 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCCC8E8678FDDFFA1E" box="[463,534,1395,1419]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
is the second for this species and the first one for 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E2932BFFBCC9008679FB40FA1E" box="[1089,1161,1394,1419]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. As suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E652583932BFFBCC8118679FE84FA3A" author="Hall" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCC4A869DFE8CFA3A" box="[267,325,1430,1455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCC14869CFE05FA3A" box="[341,460,1430,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCC14869CFE05FA3A" box="[341,460,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably close ally to 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCFAD869CFBC1FA3A" authority="Talbot, 1929" authorityName="Talbot" authorityYear="1929" box="[748,1032,1430,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCFAD869CFC94FA3A" box="[748,861,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
(Talbot, 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCE85869CFBC9FA3A" box="[964,1024,1431,1455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a species only known from 
<collectingCountry id="42E318E2932BFFBCC80F869DFF21FA46" name="French Guiana" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5E652583932BFFBCCDB986B1FE3FFA46" author="Hall" box="[248,502,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCCFA86B1FE3FFA46" box="[443,502,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5E652583932BFFBCCF4386B1FCFFFA46" author="Brevignon" box="[514,822,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCFBB86B1FCFFFA46" box="[762,822,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In fact the specimen found in 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCC9DF86B0FB2FFA46" box="[1182,1254,1467,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
has a upperside pattern of both wings similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCF4386D4FDB1FA62" box="[514,632,1502,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCF4386D4FDB1FA62" box="[514,632,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas the aspect of the blue spots of both wings underside is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCDF88508FEE6F98E" box="[185,303,1538,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCDF88508FEE6F98E" box="[185,303,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on these differences, it would be possible that the specimen from 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCC9EE8508FB3EF98E" box="[1199,1271,1539,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
represents an undescribed taxon, however, considering that the male genitalia remains unknown for both 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCC98B852CFA8CF9AA" box="[1226,1349,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCC98B852CFA8CF9AA" box="[1226,1349,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCC8C5852CFF21F9F6" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCC8C5852CFF21F9F6" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the description of the specimen from 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCCFD08540FD10F9F6" box="[657,729,1611,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
as new would be inadvisable.
</paragraph>
